  					<td align=center valign="top" width=100%><br>
  						<!--#beginContent#-->
  						<table align='center' cellpadding=5 width='85%'>  <tr><td class='spti2' width='100%'>PLAYER STRATEGY - NECROMANCER</td></tr>  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><font class='dbti'>SUCCESSFUL FEAR KITING</font> - <small>Inkie, Innoruuk</td></tr>
  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><p>Fear kiting lets us take down MOB's that full groups shy away
from because they 'hit too hard'. Done right you can Fear kite
easy. Done wrong you become another Dr00d causing Death and
trains. When you find a spawn point, look at the lay of the land.
MOB's will generally follow hills, and if they do go up/down it
will always be at the same point. If you are unsure about pathing
go find a low green somewhere nearby and cast lifetap or some
other spell that will do nothing other then annoy the MOB. Pull
him to where you wanted to hunt from and Fear him. This may also
be a good time to use Shieldskin/Steelskin or whatever you have.
If you do it right from that point on your shielding is more of a
health reserve for Allure/CoB/Lich. <br>
<br>
You want to find a place where the MOB will move away from you,
then across in front of you while feared. It's also important to
make sure that his pathing makes him walk away from the spawn
area heh. If you are in an area like RM/EW there are random spawn
points all over, you just need to find your sweet spot. I'll give
you two examples for the 30-low 40's crowd.<br>
<br>
EW. Go to the Orc fort, then straight away from the entrance.
Binding out in front of the fort (but not too close) is great
because groups are almost always camping the Gate MOB's, and
there are almost never any wanderers. You will come to a little
valley with some Giant Guards and an area where a bunch of
Ulthorks and Seals spawn. The Warriors are kinda MR, the rest are
not (Hunters and Seals have very low HP for their level). Almost
straight across the valley from where the lowest level single
Giant spawns is a tree. You want to pull to there, left side
facing where you pulled from. Once you get close enough stick
Goner on him, Dark and Fear him. Now feel free to DoT. The MOB's
will go left, then go across your path while you can nuke him
with Acid Blast or SoP, then go straight up the hill past the
tree. If you get a good DoT and feel comfortable just sit and med
and watch him. I've taken Seals at 35 who had just turned Blue,
cast VoS after he was darked and Feared and let the pet finish
him. Worst case is he lives and gets all the way up the hill. To
a large open area with no roamers. Gotta suck to be him.<br>
<br>
RM. HG's are pathetic exp I think. But me at 42 and my 42 Mage
made 1K last night there in about 4 hours, so money is hard to
beat. Go to where the Giants spawn and camp on the side of the
valley directly across from where the Guards in the tower are.
When doing HG's an Ench or Mage is wonderful because of
Malise/Tash (like we need slow Clarity). Pull the MOB's to you
(best I've found is to have the other caster pull with
Tash/Malise). Then you get a MOB that has lowered MR, yet the
pets can taunt it off easy. Target the MOB and do a /pet attack
as soon as you see it. Continue to sit and med. When your pet
goes after it, it is within Darkness range. Dark and Fear it. It
will go back towards the hill, then across the hill to your
right. I generally will cast VoS on it, then go babysit the pets,
moving/sitting/moving. If Fear wears off it is now so mad at the
pet(s) hitting it that it will go after them as long as you are
not too close. Refear. The worst things I've found is that if you
cast Fear more then twice, you'd better nuke or the pets seem to
take all the exp. You still get the loot though. And since you
know exactly where he is going you can get ahead of him and sit
and med while he is getting kicked to death by the pets.<br>
<br>
I remember pre-DoT nerf with my original incarnation grouping
with a Paladin (felt sorry for him), and saying lets go kill a
Griffawn. He said no way. So I said sit and watch, and took care
of business. DoT's are NOT nerfed when the MOB is feared. So you
can solo things because of that and your pets that a Dr00d would
run out of mana on. Just remember to always check pathing before
Fear kiting, because not knowing what the MOB will do when feared
can become fatal.<br>
</p>
</td></tr>
  <tr><td class='db'>&nbsp;</td></tr>
